  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2350 mg
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/szechuan-shrimp-green-bean-stir-fry-6501fcca7686ca60ea14b5b9
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring
to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, add green beans and a
splash of water; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}. Drain.

Heat a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce},
@Sugar{1%teaspoon}, and 2 tablespoons water. Cook, stirring, until water has
evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for peanuts over
medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned,
~{4-6%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> Rinse shrimp under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or
> beef for pork; cook, stirring frequently (no need to break up shrimp into
> pieces!), until cooked through, 4-6 minutes.

Stir green beans, scallion whites, remaining ginger, and @sugar{1%teaspoon} into
pan with pork. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until
ginger is fragrant and pork is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.
TIP: If scallions begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium low.

Stir in @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and 1/4
cup water. Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}
more. Turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with stir-fry. Sprinkle with scallion greens
and peanuts. Serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.